<h2 class="lower">&lt;br&gt; &lt;hr&gt;</h2>
<div align="left">
    Two elements that you'll use occasionally and will want to know about are
    &lt;br&gt; and &lt;hr&gt;:<br>
    &lt;br&gt; creates a line break in a paragraph; it is the only way to force
    a rigid structure in a situation where you want a series of fixed short
    lines.
    <br>
    &lt;hr&gt; elements create a horizontal rule in the document that denotes a
    thematic change in the text.
</div>